== Cultural Properties ==
=== National Historic Sites and Scenic Spots ===
* {{ill|Wakaura|ja|和歌浦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakaura|qq=}} – The shrine grounds of Shiogama Shrine are included in the national historic site and scenic spot designated area of Wakaura.

== Transportation ==
* From {{ill|Nankai Electric Railway|ja|南海電気鉄道|lt=Nankai|lt_ja=南海|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nankai Electric Railway|qq=}}’s {{ill|Wakayama City Station|ja|和歌山市駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakayama City Station|qq=}} and from {{ill|West Japan Railway Company|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|lt=JR|lt_ja=JR|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/West Japan Railway Company|qq=}}’s {{ill|Wakayama Station|ja|和歌山駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakayama Station|qq=}}, take the {{ill|Wakayama Bus|ja|和歌山バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakayama Bus|qq=}} bound for Shin-Wakaura and alight immediately at ‘Tamatsushima Shrine Front’.

